dspuNodeRsrb.name: dspuNodeRsrb
dspuNodeRsrb.description: RSRB feature enabled/disabled for the DSPU node. TRUE -> RSRB feature enabled FALSE -> RSRB feature disabled If the RSRB feature is enabled, the following object values must be valid (i.e. non-zero): - dspuNodeRsrbLocalVirtualRing - dspuNodeRsrbBridgeNumber - dspuNodeRsrbTargetVirtualRing - dspuNodeRsrbVirtualMacAddress

dspuNodeRsrbLocalVirtualRing.name: dspuNodeRsrbLocalVirtualRing
dspuNodeRsrbLocalVirtualRing.description: Local virtual ring number used by the DSPU node. LocalVirtualRing is zero if RSRB is not enabled.

dspuNodeRsrbBridgeNumber.name: dspuNodeRsrbBridgeNumber
dspuNodeRsrbBridgeNumber.description: Bridge number connecting the DSPU LocalVirtualRing with the RSRB TargetVirtualRing. Currently, the only valid BridgeNumber supported is 1. BridgeNumber must be one if RSRB is enabled. BridgeNumber is zero if RSRB is not enabled.

dspuNodeRsrbTargetVirtualRing.name: dspuNodeRsrbTargetVirtualRing
dspuNodeRsrbTargetVirtualRing.description: Target virtual ring number used for RSRB. TargetVirtualRing is zero if RSRB is not enabled.

dspuNodeRsrbVirtualMacAddress.name: dspuNodeRsrbVirtualMacAddress
dspuNodeRsrbVirtualMacAddress.description: Virtual MAC address of the the DSPU node. VirtualMacAddress is zero if RSRB is not enabled.

dspuNodeDefaultPu.name: dspuNodeDefaultPu
dspuNodeDefaultPu.description: Default-PU feature enabled/disabled for the DSPU node. TRUE -> Default-PU feature enabled FALSE -> Default-PU feature disabled

dspuNodeDefaultPuWindowSize.name: dspuNodeDefaultPuWindowSize
dspuNodeDefaultPuWindowSize.description: Send/receive window size to be used across the link between the default-PU and a remote PU.

dspuNodeDefaultPuMaxIframe.name: dspuNodeDefaultPuMaxIframe
dspuNodeDefaultPuMaxIframe.description: Maximum size of an I-frame that can be transmitted/received across the link between the default-PU and a remote PU.

dspuNodeActivationWindow.name: dspuNodeActivationWindow
dspuNodeActivationWindow.description: Activation pacing window used by the DSPU node to limit the number of activation RUs sent for a given SAP before waiting for responses from the remote.

dspuNodeLastConfigChgTime.name: dspuNodeLastConfigChgTime
dspuNodeLastConfigChgTime.description: Timestamp of last change to DSPU configuration parameters. LastConfigChgTime reflects any change in DSPU configuration.

dspuPoolClassTable.name: dspuPoolClassTable
dspuPoolClassTable.description: Table listing defined pool classes for the DSPU node. A pool class is defined at the DSPU node as a pool of upstream LUs that may be shared among downstream PUs. Each entry in the table represents a separate pool class definition. Entries in the table may not be created/deleted; however, values in existing entries may be modified. Pool classes are created when an existing LU is defined as a member of the pool class.

dspuPoolClassEntry.name: dspuPoolClassEntry
dspuPoolClassEntry.description: Each entry represents a defined pool class.

dspuPoolClassIndex.name: dspuPoolClassIndex
dspuPoolClassIndex.description: Index of a pool class entry in the dspuPoolClassTable.

dspuPoolClassName.name: dspuPoolClassName
dspuPoolClassName.description: Name identifier of the pool class.

dspuPoolClassInactivityTimeout.name: dspuPoolClassInactivityTimeout
dspuPoolClassInactivityTimeout.description: Value (in minutes) of the inactivity timeout that will be applied to active LU sessions assigned from the pool class. The inactivity timeout feature for pooled LUs is disabled if the InactivityTimeout value is zero.

dspuPoolClassOperUpStreamLuDefs.name: dspuPoolClassOperUpStreamLuDefs
dspuPoolClassOperUpStreamLuDefs.description: Number of upstream LUs defined in the pool class.

dspuPoolClassOperDnStreamLuDefs.name: dspuPoolClassOperDnStreamLuDefs
dspuPoolClassOperDnStreamLuDefs.description: Number of downstream LUs defined in the pool class.

dspuPooledLuTable.name: dspuPooledLuTable
dspuPooledLuTable.description: Table listing all LUs defined in a specified pool class. The entries in the table provide information such that the downstream LUs in the pool can be correlated with the upstream LUs to which they may be assigned and vice versa. If all upstream LUs have been assigned, downstream LUs may be waiting for assignment. If there are no downstream LUs waiting for assignment, upstream LUs may be unassigned.

dspuPooledLuEntry.name: dspuPooledLuEntry
dspuPooledLuEntry.description: Each entry represents an LU that is defined as a member of the specified pool class.

dspuPooledLuPeerPuIndex.name: dspuPooledLuPeerPuIndex
dspuPooledLuPeerPuIndex.description: Index (dspuPuOperIndex) of the peer PU that owns the peer LU. PeerPuIndex is zero if peer LU has not been assigned.

dspuPooledLuPeerLuLocalAddress.name: dspuPooledLuPeerLuLocalAddress
dspuPooledLuPeerLuLocalAddress.description: NAU address (dspuLuOperLuLocalAddress) of the peer LU. PeerLuLocalAddress is zero if peer LU has not been assigned.

dspuPuAdminTable.name: dspuPuAdminTable
dspuPuAdminTable.description: Table listing all defined upstream/downstream PUs that are owned by the DSPU node. NOTE: The dspuPuAdminTable does not include default downstream PUs that may be dynamically created.

dspuPuAdminEntry.name: dspuPuAdminEntry
dspuPuAdminEntry.description: Each entry represents a defined upstream/downstream PU.

dspuPuAdminIndex.name: dspuPuAdminIndex
dspuPuAdminIndex.description: Index of the PU entry in the dspuPuAdminTable.

dspuPuAdminType.name: dspuPuAdminType
dspuPuAdminType.description: PU Type is either upstream or downstream.

dspuPuAdminRemoteMacAddress.name: dspuPuAdminRemoteMacAddress
dspuPuAdminRemoteMacAddress.description: MAC address of the remote PU.

dspuPuAdminRemoteSapAddress.name: dspuPuAdminRemoteSapAddress
dspuPuAdminRemoteSapAddress.description: SAP address of the remote PU.

dspuPuAdminLocalSapAddress.name: dspuPuAdminLocalSapAddress
dspuPuAdminLocalSapAddress.description: SAP address of the local PU.

dspuPuAdminXid.name: dspuPuAdminXid
dspuPuAdminXid.description: Upstream PU : XID that will be sent to the remote PU. Dnstream PU : XID that must be received from the remote PU.

dspuPuAdminXidFmt.name: dspuPuAdminXidFmt
dspuPuAdminXidFmt.description: Type of XID format used during activation of the link between this dspuNode and the remote PU.

dspuPuAdminWindowSize.name: dspuPuAdminWindowSize
dspuPuAdminWindowSize.description: Send/Receive window size to be used across the link between this dspuNode and the remote PU.

dspuPuAdminMaxIframe.name: dspuPuAdminMaxIframe
dspuPuAdminMaxIframe.description: Maximum size of an I-frame that can be transmitted/received across the link between this dspuNode and the remote PU.

dspuPuAdminLinkRetryCount.name: dspuPuAdminLinkRetryCount
dspuPuAdminLinkRetryCount.description: Number of times that the DSPU node will attempt to activate the link between the dspuNode and the remote PU.

dspuPuAdminLinkRetryTimeout.name: dspuPuAdminLinkRetryTimeout
dspuPuAdminLinkRetryTimeout.description: Value (in seconds) for the delay between link activation attempts between the dspuNode and the remote PU.

dspuPuAdminStartPu.name: dspuPuAdminStartPu
dspuPuAdminStartPu.description: Attempt link activation with the remote PU. TRUE -> Attempt link activation with remote PU. FALSE -> Do not attempt link activation with remote PU.

dspuPuAdminDlcType.name: dspuPuAdminDlcType
dspuPuAdminDlcType.description: DLC type used by the dspuNode for link activation with the remote PU.

dspuPuAdminDlcUnit.name: dspuPuAdminDlcUnit
dspuPuAdminDlcUnit.description: DLC unit used by the dspuNode for link activation with the remote PU.

dspuPuAdminDlcPort.name: dspuPuAdminDlcPort
dspuPuAdminDlcPort.description: DLC port used by the dspuNode for link activation with the remote PU.

dspuPuAdminFocalPoint.name: dspuPuAdminFocalPoint
dspuPuAdminFocalPoint.description: PU serves as a focal point for alert forwarding. TRUE -> PU serves as focal point FALSE -> PU does not serve as focal point Only an upstream PU may be defined as a focal point. Downstream PUs can never be defined as a focal point; FocalPoint is always FALSE for downstream PUs. The DSPU node may define only one upstream PU as a focal point PU.

dspuPuAdminRowStatus.name: dspuPuAdminRowStatus
dspuPuAdminRowStatus.description: Used by a Management Station to create or delete the row entry in the dspuPuAdminTable following the RowStatus textual convention. Upon successful creation of the row, an Agent automatically creates a corresponding entry in the dspuPuOperTable. The Management Station can set the value to 'destroy (6)' and the Agent will then delete the rows corresponding to this PU from the dspuPuAdminTable and dspuPuOperTable.

dspuPuAdminRemoteAddress.name: dspuPuAdminRemoteAddress
dspuPuAdminRemoteAddress.description: Poll address, DLCI, or subscriber address associated with the remote PU.

dspuPuOperTable.name: dspuPuOperTable
dspuPuOperTable.description: Table listing all active upstream/downstream PUs that are owned by the DSPU node (including default PUs). NOTE: In addition to the explicitly defined PUs from the dspuPuAdminTable, the dspuPuOperTable also includes default downstream PUs that may be dynamically created.

dspuPuOperEntry.name: dspuPuOperEntry
dspuPuOperEntry.description: Each entry represents an active upstream/downstream PU.

dspuPuOperIndex.name: dspuPuOperIndex
dspuPuOperIndex.description: Index of the PU entry in dspuPuOperTable.

dspuPuOperType.name: dspuPuOperType
dspuPuOperType.description: PU type is either upstream or downstream.

dspuPuOperRemoteMacAddress.name: dspuPuOperRemoteMacAddress
dspuPuOperRemoteMacAddress.description: MAC address of the remote PU.

dspuPuOperRemoteSapAddress.name: dspuPuOperRemoteSapAddress
dspuPuOperRemoteSapAddress.description: SAP address of the remote PU.

dspuPuOperLocalSapAddress.name: dspuPuOperLocalSapAddress
dspuPuOperLocalSapAddress.description: SAP address of the local PU.

dspuPuOperXid.name: dspuPuOperXid
dspuPuOperXid.description: Upstream PU : XID that was sent to the remote PU. Dnstream PU : XID that was received from the remote PU.

dspuPuOperXidFmt.name: dspuPuOperXidFmt
dspuPuOperXidFmt.description: Type of XID format used during activation of the link between this dspuNode and the remote PU.

dspuPuOperWindowSize.name: dspuPuOperWindowSize
dspuPuOperWindowSize.description: Send/Receive window size to be used across the link between this dspuNode and the remote PU.

dspuPuOperMaxIframe.name: dspuPuOperMaxIframe
dspuPuOperMaxIframe.description: Maximum size of an I-frame that can be transmitted/received across the link between this dspuNode and the remote PU.

dspuPuOperLinkRetryCount.name: dspuPuOperLinkRetryCount
dspuPuOperLinkRetryCount.description: Number of times that the DSPU node will attempt to activate the link between the dspuNode and the remote PU.

dspuPuOperLinkRetryTimeout.name: dspuPuOperLinkRetryTimeout
dspuPuOperLinkRetryTimeout.description: Value (in seconds) for the delay between link activation attempts between the dspuNode and the remote PU.

dspuPuOperStartPu.name: dspuPuOperStartPu
dspuPuOperStartPu.description: Attempt link activation with the remote PU. TRUE -> Attempt link activation with remote PU. FALSE -> Do not attempt link activation with remote PU.

dspuPuOperDlcType.name: dspuPuOperDlcType
dspuPuOperDlcType.description: DLC type used by the dspuNode for link activation with the remote PU.

dspuPuOperDlcUnit.name: dspuPuOperDlcUnit
dspuPuOperDlcUnit.description: DLC unit used by the dspuNode for link activation with the remote PU.

dspuPuOperDlcPort.name: dspuPuOperDlcPort
dspuPuOperDlcPort.description: DLC port used by the dspuNode for link activation with the remote PU.

dspuPuOperFocalPoint.name: dspuPuOperFocalPoint
dspuPuOperFocalPoint.description: PU serves as a focal point for alert forwarding. TRUE -> PU serves as focal point FALSE -> PU does not serve as focal point Only an upstream PU may be defined as a focal point. Downstream PUs can never be defined as a focal point; FocalPoint is always FALSE for downstream PUs. The DSPU node may define only one upstream PU as a focal point PU.

dspuPuOperState.name: dspuPuOperState
dspuPuOperState.description: Operational state of PU is either active or inactive.

dspuPuOperFsmState.name: dspuPuOperFsmState
dspuPuOperFsmState.description: Current FSM state of the PU as follows: linkReset - Link is in reset state - not connected linkPendConnOut - Pending ConnectOut to establish link linkPendConnIn - Pending ConnectIn to establish link linkPendXid - Pending XID negotiation on the link linkXidNeg - XID negotiation proceeding on link linkConnOut - ConnectOut link activation linkConnIn - ConnectIn link activation linkConnected - Link connected, PU inactive puPendAct - Link connected, PU pending activation puActive - Link connected, PU active puBusy - Link connected, PU busy puPendInact - Link connected, PU pending deactivation linkPendDisc - Pending disconnect of link linkPendClose - Pending close of link station

dspuPuOperStartTime.name: dspuPuOperStartTime
dspuPuOperStartTime.description: Timestamp of PU activation (when ACTPU +rsp received).

dspuPuOperLastStateChgTime.name: dspuPuOperLastStateChgTime
dspuPuOperLastStateChgTime.description: TimeStamp of last PU state change between active<->inactive.

dspuPuOperRemoteAddress.name: dspuPuOperRemoteAddress
dspuPuOperRemoteAddress.description: Poll address, DLCI, or subscriber address associated with the remote PU.

dspuPuStatsTable.name: dspuPuStatsTable
dspuPuStatsTable.description: Table listing the statistics recorded for each PU.

dspuPuStatsEntry.name: dspuPuStatsEntry
dspuPuStatsEntry.description: Each entry represents an active upstream/downstream PU and has a corresponding entry in the dspuPuOperTable.

dspuPuStatsSentBytes.name: dspuPuStatsSentBytes
dspuPuStatsSentBytes.description: Number of bytes sent by this PU.

dspuPuStatsRcvdBytes.name: dspuPuStatsRcvdBytes
dspuPuStatsRcvdBytes.description: Number of bytes received by this PU.

dspuPuStatsSentFrames.name: dspuPuStatsSentFrames
dspuPuStatsSentFrames.description: Number of frames sent by this PU.

dspuPuStatsRcvdFrames.name: dspuPuStatsRcvdFrames
dspuPuStatsRcvdFrames.description: Number of frames received by this PU.

dspuPuStatsSentNegativeRsps.name: dspuPuStatsSentNegativeRsps
dspuPuStatsSentNegativeRsps.description: Number of negative responses sent by this PU.

dspuPuStatsRcvdNegativeRsps.name: dspuPuStatsRcvdNegativeRsps
dspuPuStatsRcvdNegativeRsps.description: Number of negative responses received by this PU.

dspuPuStatsActiveLus.name: dspuPuStatsActiveLus
dspuPuStatsActiveLus.description: Number of active LUs on this PU (LU becomes active when ACTLU +rsp received).

dspuPuStatsInactiveLus.name: dspuPuStatsInactiveLus
dspuPuStatsInactiveLus.description: Number of inactive LUs on this PU (LU is inactive until ACTLU rq or ACTLU +rsp received).

dspuPuStatsBindLus.name: dspuPuStatsBindLus
dspuPuStatsBindLus.description: Number of LUs on this PU which are active-in-session. (LU is active-in-session when BIND rq received)

dspuPuStatsActivationFailures.name: dspuPuStatsActivationFailures
dspuPuStatsActivationFailures.description: Number of activation failures for this PU.

dspuPuStatsLastActivationFailureReason.name: dspuPuStatsLastActivationFailureReason
dspuPuStatsLastActivationFailureReason.description: Reason for last activation failure of this PU as follows: noError - No PU activation failure has been detected otherError - Undefined error detected during PU activation internalError - Internal resources error detected during PU activation configurationError - PU configuration error - PU could not be activated puNegativeResponse - Negative ACTPU response received from remote PU puAlreadyActive - PU is already active

dspuLuAdminTable.name: dspuLuAdminTable
dspuLuAdminTable.description: Table listing all LUs owned by the PU. NOTE: The dspuLuAdminTable does not include LUs owned by default downstream PUs that may be dynamically created.

dspuLuAdminEntry.name: dspuLuAdminEntry
dspuLuAdminEntry.description: Each entry represents a defined LU owned by the PU.

dspuLuAdminLuLocalAddress.name: dspuLuAdminLuLocalAddress
dspuLuAdminLuLocalAddress.description: NAU address of the local LU.

dspuLuAdminType.name: dspuLuAdminType
dspuLuAdminType.description: LU type is either pooled or dedicated.

dspuLuAdminPoolClassName.name: dspuLuAdminPoolClassName
dspuLuAdminPoolClassName.description: Pool class to which the LU is defined as a member. The dspuLuAdminPoolClassName is valid for pooled LUs only.

dspuLuAdminPeerPuIndex.name: dspuLuAdminPeerPuIndex
dspuLuAdminPeerPuIndex.description: For downstream LUs, the PeerPuIndex identifies the upstream PU that owns the upstream LU to which this downstream LU is assigned. For upstream LUs, the PeerPuIndex identifies the downstream PU that owns the downstream LU to which this upstream LU is assigned. The PeerPuIndex is valid for dedicated LUs only; otherwise, the PeerPuIndex is zero.

dspuLuAdminPeerLuLocalAddress.name: dspuLuAdminPeerLuLocalAddress
dspuLuAdminPeerLuLocalAddress.description: For downstream LUs, the PeerLuLocalAddress identifies the NAU address of the upstream LU to which this downstream LU is assigned. For upstream LUs, the PeerLuLocalAddress identifies the NAU address of the downstream LU to which this upstream LU is assigned. The PeerLuLocalAddress is valid for dedicated LUs only; otherwise, the PeerLuLocalAddress is zero.

dspuLuAdminRowStatus.name: dspuLuAdminRowStatus
dspuLuAdminRowStatus.description: Used by a Management Station to create or delete the row entry in the dspuLuAdminTable following the RowStatus textual convention. Upon successful creation of the row, an Agent automatically creates a corresponding entry in the dspuLuOperTable. The Management Station can set the value to 'destroy (6)' and the Agent will then delete the rows corresponding to this LU from the dspuLuAdminTable and the dspuLuOperTable.

dspuLuOperTable.name: dspuLuOperTable
dspuLuOperTable.description: Table listing all LUs owned by the PU. NOTE: In addition to the LUs owned by explicitly defined PUs from the dspuLuAdminTable, the dspuLuOperTable also includes the LUs owned by default downstream PUs that may be dynamically created.

dspuLuOperEntry.name: dspuLuOperEntry
dspuLuOperEntry.description: Each entry represents a defined LU owned by the PU.

dspuLuOperLuLocalAddress.name: dspuLuOperLuLocalAddress
dspuLuOperLuLocalAddress.description: NAU address of the local LU.

dspuLuOperType.name: dspuLuOperType
dspuLuOperType.description: LU type is either pooled or dedicated.

dspuLuOperPoolClassName.name: dspuLuOperPoolClassName
dspuLuOperPoolClassName.description: Pool class to which the LU is defined as a member. The dspuLuOperPoolClassName is valid for pooled LUs only.

dspuLuOperPeerPuIndex.name: dspuLuOperPeerPuIndex
dspuLuOperPeerPuIndex.description: For downstream LUs, the PeerPuIndex identifies the upstream PU that owns the upstream LU to which this downstream LU is assigned. For upstream LUs, the PeerPuIndex identifies the downstream PU that owns the downstream LU to which this upstream LU is assigned. If PeerPuIndex is zero, the LU is a pooled LU and has not been assigned a peer LU from the pool.

dspuLuOperPeerLuLocalAddress.name: dspuLuOperPeerLuLocalAddress
dspuLuOperPeerLuLocalAddress.description: For downstream LUs, the PeerLuLocalAddress identifies the NAU address of the upstream LU to which this downstream LU is assigned. For upstream LUs, the PeerLuLocalAddress identifies the NAU address of the downstream LU to which this upstream LU is assigned. If the PeerLuLocalAddress is zero, the LU is a pooled LU and has not been assigned a peer LU from the pool.

dspuLuOperState.name: dspuLuOperState
dspuLuOperState.description: Operational state of LU is either active or inactive.

dspuLuOperFsmState.name: dspuLuOperFsmState
dspuLuOperFsmState.description: Current FSM state of the LU as follows: reset - neither dnLu or upLu active dnLuStarted - dnLu active, upLu inactive upLuActive - upLu active, dnLu inactive dnLuPendAct - dnLu pending activation, upLu active-unavailable dnLuActUnav - dnLu active-unavailable, upLu active-available upLuPendAvail - upLu pending-available bothAvail - both upLu and dnLu active-available dnLuPendInact - dnLu pending inactive upLuPendInact - upLu pending inactive luInactivityTimeout - inactivity Timeout on LU-to-LU session dnInactivityPendInact - dnLu pending inactive from inactivity timeout

dspuLuOperSessionState.name: dspuLuOperSessionState
dspuLuOperSessionState.description: Operational state of LU session is either bound or unbound.

dspuLuOperLastActivationFailureReason.name: dspuLuOperLastActivationFailureReason
dspuLuOperLastActivationFailureReason.description: Reason for last activation failure of this PU as follows: noError - No LU activation failure has been detected otherError - Undefined error detected during LU activation luNegativeResponse - Negative ACTLU response received from remote LU

dspuSapTable.name: dspuSapTable
dspuSapTable.description: Table listing the SAPs that are enabled for the DSPU node.

dspuSapEntry.name: dspuSapEntry
dspuSapEntry.description: Each entry represents an enabled SAP for the DSPU node.

dspuSapAddress.name: dspuSapAddress
dspuSapAddress.description: SAP address of the local SAP.

dspuSapType.name: dspuSapType
dspuSapType.description: Local SAP type is either upstreamSap or downstreamSap.

dspuSapDlcType.name: dspuSapDlcType
dspuSapDlcType.description: DLC type of the adapter that owns the local SAP.

dspuSapDlcUnit.name: dspuSapDlcUnit
dspuSapDlcUnit.description: DLC unit of the adapter that owns the local SAP.

dspuSapDlcPort.name: dspuSapDlcPort
dspuSapDlcPort.description: DLC port of the adapter that owns the local SAP.

dspuSapOperState.name: dspuSapOperState
dspuSapOperState.description: Operational state of the local SAP as follows: - sapClosed - sapOpening - sapOpened - sapClosing

dspuSapRowStatus.name: dspuSapRowStatus
dspuSapRowStatus.description: This object is used by a Management Station to create or delete the row entry in the dspuSapTable following the RowStatus textual convention. The Management Station can set the value to 'destroy (6)' and the Agent will then delete the rows corresponding to this SAP from the dspuSapTable. The local SAP address is enabled on the specified adapter when a row entry in the dspuSapTable is created.

newdspuPuStateChangeTrap.name: newdspuPuStateChangeTrap
newdspuPuStateChangeTrap.description: Generated when the operational state of the PU changes between active<-->inactive. The following information is returned: dspuPuOperName -> PU name dspuPuOperState -> Current operational state of the PU

newdspuPuActivationFailureTrap.name: newdspuPuActivationFailureTrap
newdspuPuActivationFailureTrap.description: Generated whenever a PU activation failure is detected. The following information is returned: dspuPuOperName -> PU name dspuPuOperState -> Current operational state of the PU dspuPuStatsLastActivationFailureReason -> Reason for PU activation failure

newdspuLuStateChangeTrap.name: newdspuLuStateChangeTrap
newdspuLuStateChangeTrap.description: Generated when the operational state of the LU changes between active<-->inactive. The following information is returned: dspuPuOperName -> PU name dspuLuOperState -> Current operational state of the LU

dspuLuActivationFailureTrap.name: dspuLuActivationFailureTrap
dspuLuActivationFailureTrap.description: Generated whenever an LU activation failure is detected. The following information is returned: dspuPuOperName -> PU name dspuLuOperState -> Current operational state of the LU dspuLuOperLastActivationFailureReason -> Reason for LU activation failure

dspuSapStateChangeTrap.name: dspuSapStateChangeTrap
dspuSapStateChangeTrap.description: Generated when the operational state of the SAP changes between 'open' or 'closed'. The following information is returned: dspuSapOperDlcType -> DLC type of the adapter on which SAP is located dspuSapOperDlcUnit -> Unit ID of the adapter on which SAP is located dspuSapOperDlcPort -> Port ID of the adapter on which SAP is located dspuSapOperAddress -> SAP address dspuSapOperState -> Current operational state of the SAP
